<P>The &s;econd is <HI>Richard H<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">bert<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">rn,</HI> who was al&s;o an ancient Preacher and Writer among&s;t the <HI>Quakers,</HI> and who (as did al&s;o <HI>Edward Burrough</HI>) dyed &s;o long ago, as in the year 1662. In his discour&s;e with King <HI>Charles</HI> the &s;econd, the King asked him thus, as may be &s;een in the&punc; printed account p. <HI>King.</HI> How do you own Magi&s;trates and Magi&s;tracy?
