<P>In p. 88. he publi&s;heth a letter (or at lea&s;t part of one) in the name of <HI>G. F.</HI> relating to a book of <HI>Tho. Budd's.</HI> Now that letter I know not that ever I have &s;een, therefore, for divers rea&s;ons before given, I &s;hall not credit his quo|tation, &s;o much as to take any farther notice of it.</P>
<P>In p. 90. he produceth a quotation, &s;aid to be taken out of <HI>Richard. Hubberthorn</HI>'s. <HI>Works,</HI> wherein the &s;aid <HI>R. H.</HI> blaming a Prie&s;t, &s;aith,
