<P N="10">10 <HI>thly</HI> Fal&s;e it is which he offers in p. 37. as <HI>W: P's San|dy Foundation</HI> p: 21. Chri&s;t as man was finite, viz. came to an end. For the&s;e words, viz: <HI>came to an end,</HI> are not <HI>W: P's.</HI></P>
<P N="11">11 <HI>thly</HI> An abominable fal&s;hood it is, that in <HI>Sandy Foun|dation</HI> p. 20. <HI>W: P:</HI> calls Chri&s;t, <HI>The finite and impote<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"> creature,</HI> &s;ee p. 38. and many other places of his book.</P>
