<Q>But <HI>VV: P:</HI> makes the benefit of his coming to be no more but to &s;hew man more plain what he &s;aw before as through a gla&s;s.</Q>
It being al&s;o contrary to what he him&s;elf hath cited as his wo<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ds in the &s;ame page.</P>
<P N="13">13 <HI>thly</HI> Fal&s;e it is which he a&s;&s;erts in p. 102, viz,
